race.comment: Very wary of NZ import SKYCATCHER (3) for the Price & Kent Jnr yard. He won his most recent start at Te Aroha by nearly 7 lengths and the stable usually have them ready to go first up. The track should still be in the soft range here and that will definitely suit. He can win this first time out. COSMIC CHARGER (13) is racing consistently and draws well having broken his maiden two back, following it up with a narrow miss in easier company at Echuca. He can settle closer and challenge here. LIM'S SMYTHE (2) was better last time here in a strong race, finishing on the heels of some better performed mares. Back a notch in grade, he looks well placed. LYGON STREET LUIGI (7) was first up off a short break at Kyneton and struck heavy ground, battling away fairly late. He'll be fitter and up on what looks a fairly moderate tempo.
